history.content: Are you interested in CRISPR, multi-omics, biostatistics, or other exciting topics in computational biology? Here at ULAB, a club on campus that helps students prepare for on-campus research opportunities, we are launching a computational biology DeCal for the spring semester and are seeking mentors/mentees to join us! A little bit about the course: The purpose of this course in computational biology is to give undergraduates an opportunity to gain fundamental research skills, explore relevant background knowledge, and conduct their own research project in groups. Our goal is to help students feel confident and prepared to seek out on-campus opportunities in the exciting field of computational biology. Also, mentors/mentees get 2 units through IB 98!! Get more info & apply here: tinyurl.com/ULABCompBioSp21 Attend our infosession here: https://www.facebook.com/events/418934972858921
history.subject: ULAB: Computational Biology is seeking mentors & mentees for Spring 2021!
